definitions.definition: An ethnically Somali geographic region of East Africa comprising Somalia , Djibouti , and parts of Ethiopia .

A geographic region and de facto independent unrecognized state in East Africa , internationally recognized as part of Somalia ; formerly the Somali Coast Protectorate . Official name: Republic of Somaliland .

main_definition: An ethnically Somali geographic region of East Africa comprising Somalia , Djibouti , and parts of Ethiopia .
